abstract: WASHINGTON, Jan, 1, 1882. The annual estimate by the Director of  the Mint of the values of foreign coins for 1882 makes only two changes from the values as shown in the Treasury circular of Jan. 1, 1881. The Austrian florin and the Japanese yen are each reduced 1 mill. The gourde, the monetary unit of Hayti, is added to the list of foreign,coins, and its valuation placed at 96.5 cents.

abstract: DETROIT, Mich., Jan. 25.--Floyd Whitney was arrested in this city last night charged with having murdered Warren Stafford at Chatham, Tioga County, Penn., on July 25, 1880. He admits having killed Stafford, but says he acted under great provocation and did not intend to take his life. Since the murder Whitney has been a fugitive in Colorado and various parts of this State. He will be taken back to Pennsylvania.
